Once again Jesus went out beside the Sea of Galilee, and a great crowd followed him. He began to teach them.
Then he went out a little further, and saw Levi the son of Alphaeus sitting at the tax office. And he said to him, "Follow me." So he got up and followed him.
Then Jesus ate dinner at Levi's house. A large group of tax collectors and "sinners" ate with him and his disciples. They were among the large crowd that followed Jesus.
There were some Pharisees and scribes sitting there who were critics of Jesus. They saw him eating with "sinners" and tax collectors, so they asked his disciples, "Why does he eat with tax collectors and 'sinners'?"
Jesus heard this. So he said to them, "Those who are well don't need a doctor, but the sick do. I didn't come to call those who think they are right with God to follow me. I came to call sinners to follow me." Jesus was asked about fasting.
The disciples of John and the Pharisees fast often. Some people came to Jesus and said to him, "John's disciples fast often, and the Pharisees' disciples fast often. But your disciples do not fast. Why do they not fast?"
Jesus answered and said, "How can the guests of the bridegroom fast while the bridegroom is with them? As long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast."
But the time will come when the bridegroom will be taken from them. On that day they will fast.
